# Goa workspace config. Auto-loaded by the Makefile and by `uv` at process start.
#
# First-run: `make demo` copies this file to `.env` and randomizes the pepper
# below. You can ignore everything in this file until you want to change
# persistence or expose the hub beyond localhost.

# ─── Secrets ────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# GOA_SERVER_PEPPER is used server-side to hash participant API keys. The dev
# never types or reads this value, so on first `make demo` it gets replaced
# with a random 32-byte hex string. Leave the placeholder here as a signal to
# the bootstrap script.
GOA_SERVER_PEPPER=dev-pepper

# GOA_ADMIN_TOKEN gates the hub's /admin/* routes (timeline, task inspection,
# participant directory). The dashboard prompts for this in production builds;
# the dev dashboard auto-fills it from this file. Kept as a short memorable
# string so you can also paste it into curl. Rotate before deploying.
GOA_ADMIN_TOKEN=dev-admin-token

# ─── Persistence ────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# `GOA_DATABASE_URL` selects the storage backend by URL scheme. Pick ONE block
# below; the recommended SQLite default is uncommented.

# (1) In-memory — fastest start, state vanishes on restart. Good for a first
#     poke at the hub or for transient tests. Sub-tasks, pending state, and
#     the event log all live in process memory.
# GOA_DATABASE_URL=

# (2) SQLite — single file on disk, survives restarts. Default for local dev.
#     Demo state is wiped by `make demo-clean`. ← recommended
GOA_DATABASE_URL=sqlite:./goa.db

# (3) Postgres / Supabase — multi-process, production-shaped. Requires a
#     reachable Postgres (Supabase project, RDS, Neon, self-hosted) on a
#     direct connection (port 5432; transaction-mode poolers are not
#     supported). Schema is applied on first connect — no manual migration.
# GOA_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@host:5432/goa
#
#     With Postgres you'll usually also want blobs (large attachments) on S3
#     instead of inline in the DB. Uncomment the block below if so.
# GOA_BLOB_BACKEND=s3
# GOA_BLOB_S3_BUCKET=
# GOA_BLOB_S3_REGION=
# GOA_BLOB_S3_ACCESS_KEY=
# GOA_BLOB_S3_SECRET_KEY=
